data.title: Astrology Birth Chart for Thakur Jugal Kishore Sinha (Jan. 1, 1908)
data.meta_description: Liz has two passions in life: astrology and relationships. As a professional astrologer, she has been featured in multiple publications such as BestLife, FoxNews, Glam, Glamour, and MindBodyGreen. She shares all her discoveries and observations on this website.
data.text:
Thakur Jugal Kishore Sinha or JK Sinha was an Indian politician, member of the first Lok Sabha and independence activist. He was elected as the member of the parliament in the 1st Lok Sabha from Muzaffarpur-North-West Bihar parliamentary constituency in 1953. He is known as the”Father of cooperative movement” in India for his contribution to the Cooperative Movement in India and on his initiation the cooperative departments in the Government were established and started by the first Prime Minister of India Pandit Jawaharlal Nehru. And his participation in the Indian independence movement was such that he had been imprisoned several times.

Thakur Jugal Kishore Sinha was born on January 1, 1908, in Sītāmarhi, Bihar, India. His birth geographical coordinates are 26° 35’ 37” North latitude and 85° 29’ 26” East longitude. Thakur Jugal Kishore Sinha passed away at the age of 71 in 1980.

Astrologically, Thakur Jugal Kishore Sinha falls under the Sun sign of Capricorn, with Aries as his Ascendant, Sagittarius as his Moon sign, and Cancer as his Black Moon Lilith sign.
